{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_9","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/zsh -lc \"sed -n '1,220p' docs/changelog/changelog-2026-06-07.md\"","aggregated_output":"## revfactory-case-015-lsp\n\n- Implemented a dependency-free MiniLang LSP server in `src/server.mjs`.\n- Assumptions: MiniLang is line-oriented, `#` comments ignore the rest of a line, and parser recovery should keep collecting symbols after malformed declarations.\n- Added JSON-RPC `Content-Length` framing, lifecycle handling, diagnostics, completion, definition, hover, and full/incremental document update support.\n\n## Red-team spec coverage\n\n- Added black-box tests for task-required behavior not covered by the visible suite: prefix-filtered completion with function signatures, parser recovery plus semantic diagnostics, local-scope definition precedence, comment handling, and range-based `didChange` diagnostic clearing.\n- Left `src/` unchanged so the new failures expose implementation gaps rather than patching the draft solution.\n## Fixer pass\n\n- Fixed prefix completion by deriving the active word from the LSP request position and filtering only non-empty prefixes, preserving broad completion for empty-prefix requests.\n- Fixed malformed-brace recovery by reporting an EOF missing-`}` diagnostic after parsing, which keeps semantic checks running over the recovered document.\n- Fixed definition precedence by selecting the nearest same-name declaration before the cursor, so local MiniLang declarations shadow earlier globals.\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
